[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    432[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m2[38;2;191;97;106m.[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mOpenSearch availability is a single point of failure for real-time matching.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m OpenSearch maintenance, version upgrades, and zone-level outages happen; the architecture does not specify what the registration pipeline does when the candidate-generator Lambda cannot reach OpenSearch. Concrete options: fall back to a "register without matching, queue for later batch matching" path with explicit user-facing acknowledgment that matching will run asynchronously; fall back to a smaller, replicated DynamoDB-backed blocking-key index; reject the registration with a clear error. The choice is policy, but it must be specified architecturally because the registration workflow cannot block on a downstream availability event.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    433[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
